Fit a polygenic hazard score (PHS) model

fit_phs.Rd

fit_phs() is a generic function that fits a PHS model from either a formula interface (similar to coxph()) or directly from a data frame with specified columns. It returns an object of class "phsfit", which can then be passed to get_hr(), get_or(), get_cindex(), etc.

Usage

fit_phs(object, ...)

# S3 method for class 'formula'
fit_phs(object, data, bootstrap.iterations = NULL, conf.level = 0.95, ...)

# S3 method for class 'data.frame'
fit_phs(
  object,
  age = "age",
  status = "status",
  phs = "phs",
  bootstrap.iterations = NULL,
  conf.level = 0.95,
  ...
)

Arguments

object

a data.frame containing the variables for phs, age, and status

...

Additional arguments (currently ignored)

data

A data.frame containing variables in the formula

bootstrap.iterations

Number of bootstrap iterations to run to generate confidence intervals.

conf.level

The confidence level to use for the confidence interval if conf.int = TRUE. Must be strictly greater than 0 and less than 1. Defaults to 0.95, which corresponds to a 95 percent confidence interval.

age

an optional string specifying the column name in data containing the age of each subject. For cases, this should be the age at event (e.g., diagnosis) and for controls this should be age of censoring (e.g., last observation). The default is "age"

status

an optional string specifying the column name in data containing case-control status (0 = censored, 1 = event). The default is "status"

phs

an optional string specifying the column name in data containing the polygenic hazard score for each subject. The default is "phs"

Value

An object of class "phsfit".
